Verses.Text:
 Let me proclaim the decree of Jehovah;
He said to me: “You are my son;
Today I have become your father.

 I will lie down and sleep;
And I will wake up in safety,
For Jehovah continues to support me.

 Rise up, O Jehovah! Save me, O my God!
For you will strike all my enemies on the jaw;
You will break the teeth of the wicked.

 For nothing they say can be trusted;
Within them is nothing but malice;
Their throat is an open grave;
They flatter with their tongue.

 I have grown weary with my sighing;
All night long I soak my bed with tears;
I flood my couch with weeping.

 Then let an enemy pursue and overtake me;
Let him trample my life down to the earth
And cause my glory to perish in the dust. (Selah)

 Rise up in your anger, O Jehovah;
Stand up against the fury of my enemies;
Awake for me, and demand that justice be done.

 I will rejoice and exult in you;
I will sing praises to your name, O Most High.
ב [Beth]

 For you defend my just cause;
You sit on your throne judging with righteousness.
ג [Gimel]

 He will judge the inhabited earth in righteousness;
He will render righteous legal decisions for the nations.
ו [Waw]

 Those knowing your name will trust in you;
You will never abandon those seeking you, O Jehovah.
ז [Zayin]

 For the One who avenges their blood remembers them;
He will not forget the cry of the afflicted.
ח [Heth]

 But the poor will not always be forgotten;
Nor will the hope of the meek ever perish.
כ [Kaph]

 His ways keep prospering,
But your judgments are beyond his understanding;
He scoffs at all his adversaries.

 See how the wicked bend the bow;
They set their arrow on the bowstring,
To shoot from the darkness those upright in heart.

 Those who say: “We will prevail with our tongues.
We use our lips as we please;
Who will be our master?”

 You make known to me the path of life.
In your presence is abundant joy;
There is happiness at your right hand forever.

 Hear my plea for justice, O Jehovah;
Pay attention to my cry for help;
Listen to my prayer spoken without deceit.

 You have examined my heart, you have inspected me by night;
You have refined me;
You will find that I have not schemed anything bad,
And my mouth has not transgressed.

 Then the earth began to shake and rock;
The foundations of the mountains trembled
And shook back and forth because he had been angered.

 Smoke ascended from his nostrils,
And a consuming fire came from his mouth;
Glowing coals blazed from him.

 Then Jehovah began to thunder in the heavens;
The Most High made his voice heard
With hailstones and fiery coals.

 The streambeds became visible;
The foundations of the land were exposed by your rebuke, O Jehovah,
By the blast of the breath from your nostrils.

 The way of the true God is perfect;
The saying of Jehovah is refined.
He is a shield to all those taking refuge in him.

 He rescues me from my angry enemies;
You lift me high above those who attack me;
You save me from the man of violence.

 He performs great acts of salvation for his king;
He displays loyal love to his anointed one,
To David and his offspring forever.

 But into all the earth their sound has gone out,
And to the ends of the inhabited earth their message.
In the heavens he has pitched a tent for the sun;

 It emerges from one end of the heavens,
And it circles to their other end;
And nothing is concealed from its heat.

 We will shout joyfully over your acts of salvation;
We will lift our banners in the name of our God.
May Jehovah fulfill all your requests.

 I am poured out like water;
All my bones are out of joint.
My heart has become like wax;
It melts deep within me.

 My strength has dried up like a piece of pottery;
My tongue sticks to my gums;
You are bringing me down to the dust of death.

 For dogs surround me;
They close in on me like a pack of evildoers,
Like a lion they are at my hands and feet.

 For he has not despised nor loathed the suffering of the oppressed one;
He has not hidden his face from him.
When he cried to him for help, he heard.

 The meek will eat and be satisfied;
Those seeking Jehovah will praise him.
May you enjoy life forever.

 All the prosperous ones of the earth will eat and will bow down;
All those going down to the dust will kneel before him;
None of them can preserve their lives.

 You prepare a table for me before my enemies.
You refresh my head with oil;
My cup is well-filled.

 Lift up your heads, you gates;
Open up, you ancient doorways,
That the glorious King may enter!

 Lift up your heads, you gates;
Open up, you ancient doorways,
That the glorious King may enter!

 Make me know your ways, O Jehovah;
Teach me your paths.
ה [He]

 The distresses of my heart have multiplied;
Free me from my anguish.
ר [Resh]

 For he will hide me in his shelter on the day of calamity;
He will conceal me in the secret place of his tent;
High on a rock he will place me.

 Now my head is high above my enemies who surround me;
I will offer sacrifices at his tent with joyful shouting;
I will sing praises to Jehovah.

 Hope in Jehovah;
Be courageous and strong of heart.
Yes, hope in Jehovah.

 The voice of Jehovah is heard over the waters;
The glorious God thunders.
Jehovah is over many waters.

 I will rejoice greatly in your loyal love,
For you have seen my affliction;
You are aware of my deep distress.

 O Jehovah, may I not be put to shame when I call on you.
May the wicked be put to shame;
May they be silenced in the Grave.

 You are a hiding place for me;
You will safeguard me from distress.
You will surround me with joyful shouts of deliverance. (Selah)

 I will praise Jehovah at all times;
His praise will be on my lips constantly.
ב [Beth]

 I will boast in Jehovah;
The meek will hear and rejoice.
ג [Gimel]

 Magnify Jehovah along with me;
Let us exalt his name together.
ד [Daleth]

 Those who looked to him became radiant;
Their faces could not be put to shame.
ז [Zayin]

 Taste and see that Jehovah is good;
Happy is the man who takes refuge in him.
י [Yod]

 Come, my sons, listen to me;
I will teach you the fear of Jehovah.
מ [Mem]

 Turn away from what is bad and do what is good;
Seek peace and pursue it.
ע [Ayin]

 They cried out, and Jehovah heard;
He rescued them from all their distresses.
ק [Qoph]

 Jehovah is close to the brokenhearted;
He saves those who are crushed in spirit.
ר [Resh]

 He is guarding all his bones;
Not one of them has been broken.
ת [Taw]

 May disaster come upon him by surprise;
May the net that he hid catch him;
May he fall into it and be destroyed.

 But when they were ill, I clothed myself with sackcloth;
I afflicted myself by fasting,
And when my prayer would return unanswered,

 But when I stumbled, they rejoiced and gathered together;
They gathered together to strike me down in ambush;
They tore me to pieces and did not keep silent.

 But let those who take pleasure in my righteousness shout joyfully;
May they constantly say:
“May Jehovah be magnified, who takes pleasure in the peace of his servant.”

 He plots hurtful schemes even on his bed.
He is set on a path that is not good;
He does not reject what is bad.

 Your righteousness is like majestic mountains;
Your judgments are like vast, deep waters.
Man and beast you preserve, O Jehovah.

 Just a little while longer, and the wicked will be no more;
You will look at where they were,
And they will not be there.

 But their sword will pierce their own heart;
Their bows will be broken.
ט [Teth]

 They will not be put to shame in the time of disaster;
In the time of famine they will have plenty.
כ [Kaph]

 But the wicked will perish;
The enemies of Jehovah will vanish like glorious pastures;
They will vanish like smoke.
ל [Lamed]

 The law of his God is in his heart;
His steps will not falter.
צ [Tsade]

 But he suddenly passed away and was gone;
I kept searching for him, and he could not be found.
ש [Shin]

 But all the transgressors will be destroyed;
The future of wicked people will be cut off.
ת [Taw]

 Those seeking my life set traps;
Those trying to harm me speak of ruin;
They mutter deception all day long.

 I was speechless and silent;
I kept quiet even about what is good,
But my pain was intense.

 Indeed, you have made my days just a few;
And my life span is as nothing before you.
Surely every man, though he seems secure, is nothing but a mere breath. (Selah)

 I remained speechless;
I could not open my mouth,
Because this was your doing.

 You correct man with punishment for his error;
You consume the things he treasures just as a moth does.
Surely every man is but a mere breath. (Selah)

 But I am helpless and poor;
May Jehovah pay attention to me.
You are my helper and my rescuer;
My God, do not delay.

 Jehovah will guard him and keep him alive.
He will be pronounced happy in the earth;
You will never turn him over to the will of his enemies.

 If one of them comes to see me, his heart speaks falsely.
He gathers something harmful to say;
Then he goes out and spreads it abroad.

 Send out your light and your truth.
May these lead me;
May they guide me to your holy mountain and to your grand tabernacle.

 And in your splendor go on to victory;
Ride in the cause of truth and humility and righteousness,
And your right hand will accomplish awe-inspiring things.

 He is bringing an end to wars throughout the earth.
He breaks the bow and shatters the spear;
He burns the military wagons with fire.

 “Give in and know that I am God.
I will be exalted among the nations;
I will be exalted in the earth.”

 He sees that even wise people die;
The stupid and the unreasoning perish together,
And they must leave their wealth to others.

 They are assigned like sheep to the Grave.
Death will shepherd them;
The upright will rule over them in the morning.
Every trace of them will fade away;
The Grave rather than a palace will be their home.

 The God of gods, Jehovah, has spoken;
He summons the earth
From the rising of the sun until its setting.

 “Listen, O my people, and I will speak;
Israel, I will bear witness against you.
I am God, your God.

 Then you will take delight in the sacrifices of righteousness,
The burnt sacrifices and the whole offerings;
Then bulls will be offered up on your altar.

 That is why God will pull you down once and for all;
He will snatch you up and tear you away from your tent;
He will uproot you from the land of the living. (Selah)

 I will praise you forever because you have taken action;
In the presence of your loyal ones,
I will hope in your name, for it is good.

 For it is not an enemy who taunts me;
Otherwise I could put up with it.
It is not a foe who has risen up against me;
Otherwise I could conceal myself from him.

 May destruction overtake them!
Let them go down alive into the Grave;
For evil resides among them and within them.

 They conceal themselves to attack;
They watch my every step,
Hoping to take away my life.

 Look! They wait to ambush me;
Strong men attack me
But not because I have revolted or sinned, O Jehovah.

 Look what pours forth from their mouth;
Their lips are like swords,
For they say: “Who is listening?”

 Do not kill them, so that my people may not forget.
By your power make them wander about;
Cause their downfall, O Jehovah, our shield.

 Finish them off in your wrath;
Finish them off, so that they are no more;
Make them know that God is ruling in Jacob and to the ends of the earth. (Selah)

 Gilʹead belongs to me, as does Manasʹseh,
And Eʹphraim is the helmet for my head;
Judah is my commander’s staff.

 For they consult together to topple him from his high position;
They take pleasure in lying.
With their mouth they bless, but inside they are cursing. (Selah)

 They hold fast to their evil intent;
They discuss how to hide their traps.
They say: “Who will see them?”

 They search out new ways of wrongdoing;
They secretly devise their shrewd strategy;
The thinking within each one’s heart is unfathomable.

 All the earth will bow down to you;
They will sing praises to you;
They will sing praises to your name.” (Selah)

 He changed the sea into dry land;
They crossed the river on foot.
There we rejoiced in him.

 You allowed mortal man to ride over us;
We came through fire and through water;
Then you brought us to a place of relief.

 As smoke is driven away, may you drive them away;
As wax melts before the fire,
So let the wicked perish before God.

 But let the righteous rejoice;
May they be overjoyed before God;
May they exult with rejoicing.

 God gives those who are alone a home to dwell in;
He leads prisoners out into prosperity.
But the stubborn must live in a parched land.

 The earth quaked;
Heaven poured down rain because of God;
This Siʹnai quaked because of God, the God of Israel.

 You ascended on high;
You carried away captives;
You took gifts in the form of men,
Yes, even stubborn ones, to reside among them, O Jah God.

 I am exhausted from calling out;
My throat has become hoarse.
My eyes have grown weary while waiting for my God.

 But I am helpless and poor;
O God, act quickly in my behalf.
You are my helper and my rescuer;
O Jehovah, do not delay.

 I have depended on you from birth;
It was you who took me from my mother’s womb.
I praise you constantly.

 I will come and tell about your mighty acts,
O Sovereign Lord Jehovah;
I will mention your righteousness, yours alone.

 Your righteousness, O God, reaches to the heights;
You have done great things;
O God, who is like you?

 Though you have made me experience much distress and calamity,
Revive me again;
Bring me up from the depths of the earth.

 There are no signs for us to see;
There is no longer any prophet,
And no one among us knows how long this will last.

 We give thanks to you, O God, we give thanks to you;
Your name is near,
And people declare your wondrous works.

 The courageous of heart have been plundered.
They have fallen asleep;
The warriors were all helpless.

 During the night I remember my song;
I ponder in my heart;
I make a diligent search.

 The waters saw you, O God;
The waters saw you and were disturbed.
And the deep waters became agitated.

 The sound of your thunder was like chariot wheels;
Flashes of lightning lit up the inhabited earth;
The earth trembled and quaked.

 Your way was through the sea,
Your path through many waters;
But your footprints could not be traced.

 When Jehovah heard them, he became furious;
A fire blazed against Jacob,
And his anger flared up against Israel

 God’s wrath flared up against them.
He put to death their strongest men;
He brought down the young men of Israel.

 He cleared a pathway for his anger.
He did not spare them from death;
And he gave them over to pestilence.

 He led them in security,
And they felt no fear;
The sea covered their enemies.

 He drove out the nations from before them;
He allotted to them an inheritance by the measuring line;
He settled the tribes of Israel in their homes.

 From tending the nursing ewes;
He made him the shepherd over Jacob, his people,
And over Israel, his inheritance.

 O God, the nations have invaded your inheritance;
They have defiled your holy temple;
They have turned Jerusalem into a heap of ruins.

 Help us, O God of our salvation,
For the sake of your glorious name;
Rescue us and forgive our sins for the sake of your name.

 Then we, your people and the flock of your pasture,
Will give thanks to you forever;
And we will declare your praise from generation to generation.

 Before Eʹphraim and Benjamin and Manasʹseh,
Do stir up your mightiness;
Come and save us.

 In your distress you called, and I rescued you;
I answered you from the thundercloud.
I tested you at the waters of Merʹibah. (Selah)

 They do not know, nor do they understand;
They are walking about in darkness;
All the foundations of the earth are being shaken.

 When they pass through the Baʹca Valley,
They make it into a place of springs;
And the early rain clothes it with blessings.

 O God, presumptuous men rise up against me;
A band of ruthless men seek to take my life,
And they have no regard for you.

 I will count Raʹhab and Babylon among those who know me;
Here are Philisʹtia and Tyre, together with Cush.
It will be said: “This is one who was born there.”

 You have driven my acquaintances far away from me;
You have made me something detestable to them.
I am trapped and cannot escape.

 My eye is worn out because of my affliction.
I call on you, O Jehovah, all day long;
To you I spread out my hands.

 From my youth on,
I have been afflicted and ready to perish;
I am numb from the terrible things you allow me to suffer.

 Your arm is mighty;
Your hand is strong;
Your right hand is exalted.

 At that time you spoke in a vision to your loyal ones and said:
“I have granted strength to a mighty one;
I have exalted a chosen one from among the people.

 May the favor of Jehovah our God be upon us;
May you prosper the work of our hands.
Yes, prosper the work of our hands.

 Indeed, look in triumph on your enemies, O Jehovah,
Look at how your enemies will perish;
All the wrongdoers will be scattered.

 Jehovah has become King!
With grandeur he is clothed;
Jehovah is clothed with strength;
He wears it like a belt.
The earth is firmly established;
It cannot be moved.

 The rivers have surged, O Jehovah,
The rivers have surged and roared;
The rivers keep surging and pounding.

 For 40 years I felt a loathing toward that generation, and I said:
“They are a people who always go astray in their hearts;
They have not come to know my ways.”

 Zion hears and rejoices;
The towns of Judah are joyful
Because of your judgments, O Jehovah.

 O you who love Jehovah, hate what is bad.
He is guarding the lives of his loyal ones;
He rescues them from the hand of the wicked.

 For Jehovah is good;
His loyal love endures forever,
And his faithfulness through all generations.

 I will not set anything worthless before my eyes.
I hate the deeds of those who deviate from what is right;
I will have nothing to do with them.

 Do not hide your face from me in my time of distress.
Incline your ear to me;
Do answer me quickly when I call.

 Surely you will rise up and show mercy on Zion,
For it is time to show her your favor;
The appointed time has come.

 They will perish, but you will remain;
Just like a garment they will all wear out.
Just like clothing you will replace them, and they will pass away.

 Praise Jah!
Give thanks to Jehovah, for he is good;
His loyal love endures forever.

 They rise up to the sky;
They plunge down to the depths.
Their courage melts away because of the impending calamity.

 Gilʹead belongs to me, as does Manasʹseh,
And Eʹphraim is the helmet for my head;
Judah is my commander’s staff.

 He will execute judgment against the nations;
He will fill the land with dead bodies.
He will crush the leader of a vast land.

 Hands they have, but they cannot feel;
Feet, but they cannot walk;
They make no sound with their throat.

 Jehovah remembers us and will bless;
He will bless the house of Israel;
He will bless the house of Aaron.

 The ropes of death encircled me;
The Grave had me in its grip.
I was overcome by distress and grief.

 For his loyal love toward us is great;
The faithfulness of Jehovah endures forever.
Praise Jah!

 I am fond of your reminders;
They are my advisers.
ד [Daleth]

 Your loyal love, O Jehovah, fills the earth;
Teach me your regulations.
ט [Teth]

 Support me as you promised,
So that I may keep living;
Do not let my hope turn into disappointment.

 The dread of you makes my body tremble;
I am in fear of your judgments.
ע [Ayin]

 Therefore, I consider every instruction from you to be right;
I hate every false path.
פ [Pe]

 Those passing by will not say:
“May the blessing of Jehovah be upon you;
We bless you in the name of Jehovah.”

 No, but I have calmed and quieted my soul
Like a weaned child with its mother;
I am contented like a weaned child.

 Praise Jah!
Praise the name of Jehovah;
Offer praise, you servants of Jehovah,

 He causes clouds to ascend from the ends of the earth;
He makes lightning for the rain;
He brings the wind out of his storehouses.

 Even when I walk in the midst of danger, you will preserve me alive.
You stretch out your hand against the anger of my enemies;
Your right hand will save me.

 Jehovah will accomplish all things in my behalf.
O Jehovah, your loyal love endures forever;
Do not forsake the works of your hands.

 Even the darkness would not be too dark for you,
But night would be as bright as the day;
Darkness is the same as light to you.

 Protect me, O Jehovah, from the hands of the wicked;
Safeguard me from violent men,
Those who scheme to trip me.

 The haughty ones hide a trap for me;
With ropes they spread out a net beside the path.
They set snares for me. (Selah)

 Do not let my heart incline to anything bad,
To share in vile deeds with evil men;
May I never feast on their delicacies.

 O Jehovah, hear my prayer;
Listen to my plea for help.
In your faithfulness and in your righteousness, answer me.

 For the enemy pursues me;
He has crushed my life into the ground.
He has caused me to dwell in darkness like those long dead.

 I remember the days of old;
I meditate on all your activity;
I eagerly ponder over the work of your hands.

 In your loyal love, put an end to my enemies;
Destroy all those harassing me,
For I am your servant.

 Stretch out your hands from above;
Rescue me and save me from the surging waters,
From the hand of the foreigners,

 All day long I will praise you;
I will praise your name forever and ever.
ג [Gimel]

 Jehovah is great and most worthy of praise;
His greatness is unsearchable.
ד [Daleth]

 Generation after generation will praise your works;
They will tell about your mighty acts.
ה [He]

 All eyes look hopefully to you;
You give them their food in its season.
פ [Pe]

 He satisfies the desire of those who fear him;
He hears their cry for help, and he rescues them.
ש [Shin]

 Jehovah is opening the eyes of the blind;
Jehovah is raising up those bowed down;
Jehovah loves the righteous.

 Jehovah is protecting the foreign residents;
He sustains the fatherless child and the widow,
But he thwarts the plans of the wicked.

 Praise Jah!
It is good to sing praises to our God;
How pleasant and fitting it is to praise him!

 He has not done so with any other nation;
They know nothing about his judgments.
Praise Jah!

 Praise Jah!
Praise Jehovah from the heavens;
Praise him in the heights.

 Praise Jah!
Sing to Jehovah a new song;
Praise him in the congregation of the loyal ones.
